# Infra Job Idempotency

- Design long-running jobs to be resumable and idempotent.
- Use durable checkpoints at stage boundaries for restart safety.
- Include deduplication keys for retry handling and event replay.
- Emit stage-level metrics (attempts, duration, failure class, recovery path).

## Operational Guardrails

- Separate transient failures from data/logic failures in retries.
- Avoid side effects before checkpoint commits.
- Ensure each pipeline stage can be rerun without duplicate writes.
